<h2>Local KHRD Help: Source linkage</h2>

<p>Source linkage in Yggdrasil means making assertions about the existance of people from sources.</p>

<h3>Source linkage contents:</h3>

<table border="1">
<tr><th>Label</th><th>Yggdrasil</th><th>Description</th><th>KHRD usage conventions and date entry guidelines</th></tr>

<tr>
  <th>Source text</th>
  <td>Source text</td>
  <td>Description/label/transcript of this source</td>
  <td></td>
</tr>

<tr>
  <th>Role</th>
  <td>label_en</td>
  <td>Label used (english)</td>
  <td>See table linkage_roles: undefined | child | father | mother | godparent | other</td>
</tr>

<tr>
  <th>Person</th>
  <td>person_fk</td>
  <td>Id of person whose existence is asserted from this source.</td>
  <td>Leave 0 if unknown.</td>
</tr>

<tr>
  <th>How sure?</th>
  <td>surety_fk</td>
  <td>Level of certainty.</td>
  <td>Wrong | unknown | possible | probable | certain.</td>
</tr>

<tr>
  <th>Person name ...</th>
  <td>s_name</td>
  <td>Person name and contextual info as mentioned in the source.</td>
  <td>Alt names of the subject, aliases, relations. Use for matricle? Searchable? These are shown in the list_mentioned function in source manager.</td>
</tr>

<tr>
  <th>Note</th>
  <td>sl_note</td>
  <td>Notes and inferences.</td>
  <td></td>
</tr>

</table>

